02:49.625 --> 02:55.061
<i>♪ What a town without pity can do ♪</i>

02:55.063 --> 03:01.034
<i>♪ If we stop to gaze upon a star ♪</i>

03:01.036 --> 03:04.371
<i>♪ People talk about how bad... ♪</i>

03:04.373 --> 03:06.540
Hi, there, handsome. You ready?

03:06.542 --> 03:08.275
How's the Salisbury steak?

03:09.360 --> 03:11.711
Have you ever eaten at Tucker's
Steakhouse across the street?

03:11.713 --> 03:12.946
Oh, sure. Not on my dime.

03:12.948 --> 03:14.915
Our porterhouse is the same exact cut.

03:14.917 --> 03:15.982
Same supplier.

03:15.984 --> 03:17.784
But that's a $50 cut.

03:17.786 --> 03:20.420
In here, it's almost half the price.

03:20.422 --> 03:22.455
I take mine medium rare.

03:24.826 --> 03:27.127
Y'all have been a breath of fresh air

03:27.129 --> 03:29.296
just as I was starting to feel homesick.

03:29.298 --> 03:30.730
Let me get your change.

03:30.732 --> 03:32.830
No, no, keep the change, please.

03:32.865 --> 03:34.481
You're a doll.

03:34.516 --> 03:36.636
Bless your hearts.

03:43.802 --> 03:45.912
Excuse me, hon.

03:45.914 --> 03:47.013
Hmm?

03:47.015 --> 03:48.148
Could we get a top-off?

03:48.150 --> 03:49.783
Oh, of course.

03:49.785 --> 03:52.285
Can I get you guys anything else?

03:52.287 --> 03:55.522
Our Fudge Blackout Cake is to die for.

03:55.524 --> 03:56.990
No, thanks, kid. We're great.

03:56.992 --> 03:58.858
You sure are.

03:58.860 --> 04:00.860
One day, when I'm sitting here
in this very diner

04:00.862 --> 04:02.462
with my future husband,

04:02.464 --> 04:07.300
I hope to look as striking
and happy as you two.

04:07.302 --> 04:10.829
[chuckles] You clocking
the moves on this one?

04:10.864 --> 04:12.672
Yeah, she's got to be racking huge tips.

04:12.674 --> 04:14.274
Hey, good to see you guys again.

04:14.276 --> 04:16.843
This is what I always order.
It's so good.

04:16.845 --> 04:18.812
Kid's a natural.

04:18.814 --> 04:23.049
<i>♪ Can do ♪</i>

04:23.051 --> 04:25.986
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:26.745 --> 04:28.855
Yeah.

04:28.857 --> 04:30.824
What?

04:30.826 --> 04:33.126
Are you kidding me?

04:33.128 --> 04:34.694
This is our only shot.

04:34.696 --> 04:35.895
Our third doesn't even arrive until...

04:35.897 --> 04:37.197
Shh.

04:37.199 --> 04:40.000
- I'll be back in one minute.
- Fine, fine. We'll wing it.

04:40.002 --> 04:45.639
- What was that?
- Our friend's leaving. Tonight.

04:45.641 --> 04:47.207
What? Let me guess.

04:47.209 --> 04:49.009
Your beloved Cy Roberts
dropped the ball again.

04:49.011 --> 04:51.344
He confused us with
Cincinnati and Akron.

04:51.346 --> 04:53.046
Thanks for nothing, Cy.

04:53.048 --> 04:54.681
Jesus.

04:54.683 --> 04:55.849
So this Cy guy,

04:55.851 --> 04:57.517
you want me to take care of him for you?

04:58.001 --> 04:59.417
That's cute, kid. Yeah.

04:59.452 --> 05:00.654
Yeah, we wish.

05:00.656 --> 05:02.822
Well, look at this table
of black and gold.

05:02.824 --> 05:05.425
Looks like we got some
fellow Panther fans here.

05:05.427 --> 05:07.494
- Whoo!
- [customers cheer]

05:07.496 --> 05:09.229
You guys want some waters?

05:09.231 --> 05:11.264
Take your time with the menu, boys.

05:11.266 --> 05:14.701
I promise I'll be right back.

05:14.703 --> 05:17.037
- Uh, can we...
- Oh, ready for a check?

05:17.039 --> 05:19.906
- Having fun?
- Of course.

05:19.908 --> 05:21.741
I mean, I love my job.

05:21.743 --> 05:23.777
- I love my customers.
- Is that a fact?

05:23.779 --> 05:25.712
Because when you drop your game face,

05:25.714 --> 05:29.749
it sure looks like you'd rather be
almost anywhere else.

05:30.519 --> 05:32.085
Yeah, maybe.

05:32.087 --> 05:34.087
[chuckles]

05:34.697 --> 05:35.689
Definitely.

05:36.555 --> 05:39.359
Think you'd be interested
in taking your game to the next level?

05:40.108 --> 05:42.762
Make some real money.

05:44.733 --> 05:46.566
I got to run, so I'll see you tomorrow.

05:46.568 --> 05:48.868
20 minutes! Let's go!

05:48.870 --> 05:51.905
[various conversations]

05:54.109 --> 05:56.776
<i>Lansdale line now
departing from track two.</i>

05:56.778 --> 05:58.945
<i>Lansdale to Phoenix Hill
and Valley Forge</i>

05:58.947 --> 06:00.747
<i>now departing from line two.</i>

06:00.749 --> 06:03.750
<i>[energetic jazzy music]</i>

06:03.752 --> 06:10.724
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:10.726 --> 06:12.726
[gasps]

06:12.728 --> 06:15.228
- Oh, my God.
- You all right?

06:15.230 --> 06:17.430
- Oh, God, it's just...
- Here, let me get that.

06:17.432 --> 06:19.432
Careful. Don't hurt yourself.

06:19.434 --> 06:20.800
- Thank you!
- No problem.

06:20.802 --> 06:22.001
What a lousy day.

06:22.003 --> 06:23.503
I mean, first day on the job,

06:23.505 --> 06:26.139
and my new boss could not have been
a bigger pain in the ass.

06:26.141 --> 06:27.807
I mean, all friggin' day, like,

06:27.809 --> 06:29.809
"Type faster. Type faster."

06:29.811 --> 06:31.778
I already type 100 words a minute.

06:31.780 --> 06:35.181
Well, trust me; you could probably
get a job anywhere.

06:35.183 --> 06:37.417
<i>- Now arriving...</i>
- That's my train.

06:37.419 --> 06:41.154
Oh, well, thank you. You're so kind.

06:41.156 --> 06:43.790
Hey, any chance I can get your number?

06:43.792 --> 06:45.425
Uh, well, sure.

06:50.327 --> 06:51.831
Don't miss your train.

07:00.568 --> 07:02.008
Not bad for ten minutes of work, huh?

07:02.908 --> 07:05.445
No. [laughs] Not bad at all.

07:05.447 --> 07:08.181
Hey, you didn't give that guy
your real number, did you?

07:08.183 --> 07:09.849
Oh, well, I gave him <i> a</i> number.

07:10.541 --> 07:12.085
To the Pottsville police station.

07:14.324 --> 07:16.856
- Any interest in doing this again?
- Sure.

07:16.858 --> 07:18.124
Parents let you stay out late?

07:18.126 --> 07:20.026
My parents barely know I'm alive.

07:20.028 --> 07:22.796
Oh. Well, they don't know
what they're missing.

07:22.798 --> 07:25.331
We'll be in touch.

07:25.333 --> 07:27.000
Okay.

07:36.812 --> 07:39.345
<i>[horn honks]</i>

07:44.085 --> 07:45.718
<i>- Oh!
- Richard.</i>

07:45.720 --> 07:47.086
<i>- Oh, I'm cramping!
- Richard.</i>

07:47.088 --> 07:48.521
<i>- I'm cramping. I'm...
- Richard!</i>

07:48.523 --> 07:50.223
Can you just lean the other way?

07:50.225 --> 07:51.925
When you got in,
you didn't have to spoon me...

07:51.927 --> 07:53.760
So that we're 69ing each other?
No, thank you.

07:53.762 --> 07:55.862
Just please move your arm
out from under my ribs.

07:55.864 --> 07:56.863
I'm in pain.

07:56.865 --> 07:57.864
Yeah, here we go.

07:57.866 --> 07:59.866
Not there! Jesus!

07:59.868 --> 08:01.034
Sorry, was that your...

08:01.036 --> 08:02.335
Yes! Yes, it was.

08:02.337 --> 08:04.037
Oh. Wow, man.

08:04.039 --> 08:05.438
I'm impressed.

08:05.440 --> 08:07.240
I had no idea.

08:07.242 --> 08:08.708
And nothing makes you happier

08:08.710 --> 08:10.710
than being scandalized
by everything that I do.

08:10.712 --> 08:12.011
Happy?

08:12.013 --> 08:14.013
You needed my help to
the tune of $10,000.

08:14.015 --> 08:16.583
Yes, I know, and I appreciate that.
I'm just saying.

08:16.585 --> 08:18.384
Doesn't sound like appreciation.

08:18.386 --> 08:19.853
I'm just saying that
whenever you're around me,

08:19.855 --> 08:20.996
I don't think you're conscious of it,

08:21.056 --> 08:23.723
but you are incapable of
drawing a nonjudgmental breath.

08:23.725 --> 08:25.124
Don't be so irascible.

08:25.126 --> 08:26.693
It is my job to tough-love you.

08:26.695 --> 08:27.861
That's not a verb.

08:27.863 --> 08:29.195
For the past three years,

08:29.197 --> 08:30.763
you have been the hottest
of all messes ever.

08:30.765 --> 08:32.899
If I didn't help you, who would?

08:32.900 --> 08:35.235
Nope, not judgmental at all. Not at all.

08:37.772 --> 08:40.106
Oh, these texts
aren't even going through.

08:40.107 --> 08:42.107
Shit.

08:42.110 --> 08:44.410
I really hope that
kid got her that note.

08:44.412 --> 08:46.045
So is the plan, like,

08:46.047 --> 08:49.749
you and Sophia live a life of crime?

08:49.751 --> 08:51.951
I don't really have a plan at the moment

08:51.953 --> 08:53.419
other than, I mean,

08:53.421 --> 08:54.954
my parents are being held hostage.

08:54.956 --> 08:56.789
Hey, I'm not judging, man.

08:56.791 --> 09:00.093
I'm just asking, 'cause, I mean,

09:00.095 --> 09:03.897
I don't think I'm cut
out for this con stuff.

09:03.899 --> 09:05.298
I mean, I could be,

09:05.300 --> 09:07.634
but I'm destined for something greater.

09:07.636 --> 09:09.836
I can feel it in my balls.

09:09.838 --> 09:12.805
Spoken like a man
destined for greatness.

09:12.807 --> 09:13.940
[both yell]

09:13.942 --> 09:15.241
God damn it!

09:15.243 --> 09:16.943
- I hate it in here!
- Me too!

09:16.945 --> 09:19.879
So give me the deets on Richard Evans.

09:19.881 --> 09:20.747
What?

09:20.749 --> 09:22.916
No. Why?

09:22.918 --> 09:24.951
I don't know. I'm intrigued.

09:24.953 --> 09:27.420
Hey, listen.

09:27.422 --> 09:28.454
He's a nice guy, okay?

09:28.456 --> 09:29.515
He's been through a lot.

09:29.591 --> 09:31.791
You're not sticking your
manicured claws into him.

09:31.793 --> 09:34.260
Mm-hmm.

09:34.262 --> 09:35.461
[chuckles]

09:35.463 --> 09:36.763
What's so funny?

09:36.765 --> 09:39.999
I can't believe the
real Alice showed up.

09:40.001 --> 09:41.501
She's not Alice.

09:41.503 --> 09:44.671
Well, she's the OG Alice.

09:44.673 --> 09:46.172
Maybe it's a sign.

09:46.174 --> 09:47.586
A sign for what?

09:47.621 --> 09:50.944
I don't know. That, like,
shit's gonna be awesome again.

09:50.946 --> 09:52.679
Maybe it all happened...

09:52.681 --> 09:53.780
For a reason

09:53.782 --> 09:55.848
that Laszlo stormed off in a huff.

09:55.850 --> 09:57.016
You were always in that cycle,

09:57.018 --> 09:58.284
even when you were dating.

09:58.286 --> 09:59.819
I suppose.

09:59.821 --> 10:02.188
What do you think about Laszlo?

10:02.190 --> 10:03.790
He's your husband.

10:03.792 --> 10:05.291
Answer the question.

10:05.293 --> 10:07.894
I think he's...

10:07.896 --> 10:09.696
your husband.

10:09.698 --> 10:12.832
I just don't know if
that's true anymore.

10:14.903 --> 10:17.236
Oh, Poops, I'm sorry.

10:17.238 --> 10:19.839
Oh, it's okay.

10:20.700 --> 10:22.208
I'm fine. It's just...

10:22.210 --> 10:25.478
[sighs] Ugh.

10:25.480 --> 10:27.146
But that Richard.

10:27.148 --> 10:28.982
The way he's looking at me,

10:28.984 --> 10:32.501
it was so sweet and open,

10:32.536 --> 10:34.387
so decidedly not Laszlo.

10:34.389 --> 10:37.223
I don't like where this is going.

10:37.225 --> 10:38.758
It's not going anywhere.

10:38.760 --> 10:40.426
Yet.

10:40.428 --> 10:42.413
Oy vey.

10:42.448 --> 10:45.391
And on top of everything,
you're speaking Hebrew?

10:46.238 --> 10:47.200
<i>I'm going on a picnic,</i>

10:47.202 --> 10:51.404
and I'm bringing an apple,
a brontosaurus,

10:51.406 --> 10:56.008
a crash helmet,
a diorama, an egg, and...

10:56.101 --> 10:57.100
some fish.

10:57.135 --> 10:59.345
I'm going on a picnic,
and I'm bringing an apple,

10:59.347 --> 11:01.247
a brontosaurus, a...

11:01.249 --> 11:03.249
<i>[brakes squeak softly]</i>

11:03.251 --> 11:05.184
<i>[man speaking in Spanish]</i>

11:05.186 --> 11:06.786
Oh, are we stopping?

11:06.788 --> 11:09.389
- Are we stopping?
- Shh!

11:09.391 --> 11:11.624
- <i>[dog barks]</i>
- Holy shit.

11:11.626 --> 11:13.793
It's probably just a spot check.

11:13.795 --> 11:15.962
- Play dead.
- What?

11:15.964 --> 11:19.065
<i>[men speaking in Spanish]</i>

11:20.702 --> 11:23.269
