15:20.991 --> 15:23.425
Yo, yo, back up, dude.
You're, like, right next to me.

15:23.427 --> 15:25.026
Ah, shit.

15:25.028 --> 15:28.530
Oh! Oh, come on.

15:28.532 --> 15:30.699
The fricking guy's, like,
yelling at us in Spanish.

15:30.701 --> 15:32.400
I know; it was like being in a tomb.

15:32.402 --> 15:34.402
Right? It's like
we were stuck in a foxhole.

15:34.404 --> 15:35.937
I'm definitely getting cremated.

15:35.939 --> 15:38.173
I thought we had
some nice moments, actually.

15:38.175 --> 15:39.574
Guys.

15:39.576 --> 15:42.577
There are two things
we have to accomplish.

15:42.579 --> 15:44.628
First, I have to rescue
my family from Max.

15:44.663 --> 15:46.819
No, wait, wait.
You're not doing this by yourself.

15:46.851 --> 15:48.383
It's my family.

15:48.385 --> 15:51.219
If I show up with anybody else,
it could (BLEEP) everything up.

15:51.221 --> 15:53.221
Agreed?

15:53.223 --> 15:54.651
Well, shit, man, I guess.

15:54.659 --> 15:57.331
Good. Which brings me
to goal number two.

15:57.361 --> 16:00.028
You guys have to go to
Scottsdale and get the ring.

16:00.030 --> 16:02.798
We may need the leverage,
and we definitely need the money.

16:03.267 --> 16:05.641
When you're done and assuming
I made peace with Max,

16:05.670 --> 16:07.576
we meet up someplace discreet.

16:07.611 --> 16:09.804
We just have to figure out where.

16:09.806 --> 16:11.740
Hey, what's going on
at the cabin these days?

16:11.742 --> 16:13.375
Ugh, Mom is insisting

16:13.377 --> 16:15.577
that all the cousins
come up for Labor Day.

16:15.579 --> 16:16.611
And I mean all of them.

16:17.116 --> 16:20.582
- I mean right now.
- Oh, nothing.

16:20.584 --> 16:22.355
Why don't you guys use it as a hideout?

16:22.453 --> 16:23.268
Gee, good idea.

16:23.288 --> 16:25.367
It's in way upstate New York,
like in the woods woods.

16:25.423 --> 16:27.455
Good, then we have a plan.

16:27.457 --> 16:31.659
Richard, I need one thing first.

16:31.661 --> 16:34.662
<i>[light jazzy music]</i>

16:34.664 --> 16:41.669
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:41.671 --> 16:45.040
Hey, what kind of bra are you wearing?

16:45.042 --> 16:48.677
Agent Provocateur, Lorna cut, nude.

16:48.779 --> 16:51.679
And you're, what, 34B?

16:51.681 --> 16:53.214
Yes, sir.

16:53.216 --> 16:56.684
Cool. Take it off.

16:56.686 --> 16:59.721
Just let me know if anyone
comes within 40 to 50 feet.

16:59.773 --> 17:02.073
Look casual.

17:02.075 --> 17:04.742
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:04.744 --> 17:08.413
One Mississippi, two Mississippi,

17:08.415 --> 17:09.548
three Mississ...

17:09.550 --> 17:11.916
Ah, yeah! Still got it.

17:11.919 --> 17:14.819
You certainly do.

17:16.390 --> 17:18.223
Did you reach Sophia?

17:18.224 --> 17:19.691
No, I called, like, five times.

17:19.693 --> 17:21.810
I can't tell if it's going to voicemail
or it's not in service.

17:21.896 --> 17:23.406
She's probably pissed
we left without her.

17:23.497 --> 17:25.096
Yeah, that's what I said.

17:25.098 --> 17:26.865
- Thank you.
- You'll find her.

17:30.737 --> 17:32.304
Be careful, okay?

17:32.306 --> 17:33.638
Yes, Mom.

17:33.640 --> 17:35.674
I promise to check in along the way.

17:37.077 --> 17:38.143
Hey, don't speed.

17:38.145 --> 17:39.711
Yeah, don't speed.

17:39.713 --> 17:41.479
Maybe you should have
hotwired a minivan.

17:41.481 --> 17:43.114
- Gross.
- Please.

17:43.116 --> 17:44.816
Always forward.

17:44.818 --> 17:46.251
Yeah.

17:46.253 --> 17:49.287
I cannot wait to tell Mom...

17:49.289 --> 17:50.655
Here.

17:50.657 --> 17:53.558
Try not to, you know, kill anybody

17:53.560 --> 17:55.493
or... or die.

17:55.495 --> 17:57.028
Excellent advice.

18:06.573 --> 18:09.074
<i>[birds chirping]</i>

18:12.880 --> 18:15.914
<i>[gentle music]</i>

18:15.916 --> 18:22.954
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:32.366 --> 18:34.900
<i>Maddie Jonson at long last.</i>

18:34.902 --> 18:36.468
<i>A pleasure to finally meet you.</i>

18:36.470 --> 18:37.558
<i>You too.</i>

18:37.638 --> 18:39.475
<i>Thank you for the consideration.</i>

18:39.540 --> 18:41.306
Max tells me you're a natural.

18:41.308 --> 18:42.974
A phenom, he said.

18:43.836 --> 18:45.877
I do what I can.

18:46.465 --> 18:48.647
You have a worldly way about you.

18:48.649 --> 18:52.217
Would you call yourself an old soul?

18:52.219 --> 18:54.519
I never really thought about it.

18:54.521 --> 18:56.554
I suppose I could be.

18:56.556 --> 19:01.493
Ah, an outsider and an observer?

19:01.495 --> 19:04.496
Yes, I have always felt that way.

19:04.498 --> 19:07.532
Max, Sally, you and me,

19:07.534 --> 19:09.501
we're seekers.

19:09.503 --> 19:11.336
- Seekers?
- Mm-hmm.

19:11.338 --> 19:13.638
We want to live life by our own rules

19:13.640 --> 19:15.173
and explore the limits of control.

19:15.175 --> 19:17.575
Did you remind her
not to say more than she has to?

19:17.577 --> 19:19.577
Yes, she's going to do fine.

19:19.579 --> 19:21.579
Like, you said,
the Doctor has an eye for talent.

19:21.581 --> 19:23.848
I know. I know.

19:23.850 --> 19:27.052
But the Doctor can be
overly discriminating.

19:27.054 --> 19:29.921
Do you know what the
greatest con of all is?

19:31.325 --> 19:34.326
Love.

19:34.328 --> 19:36.061
Love?

19:36.063 --> 19:38.396
You have a unique ability.

19:38.398 --> 19:43.001
You instinctually grasp what lies behind
a person's desires and longing.

19:43.003 --> 19:45.270
Very rare.

19:45.272 --> 19:50.342
That talent will allow us to explore
some interesting opportunities.

19:53.880 --> 19:56.414
Your first opportunity.

19:56.416 --> 19:58.717
Everything you need to know is inside.

20:02.723 --> 20:05.223
Cute.

20:05.225 --> 20:06.725
I'm supposed to...

20:06.727 --> 20:08.593
Learn about him, study him,

20:08.595 --> 20:12.397
and then maybe run into him
somewhere appropriate.

20:12.399 --> 20:13.999
See where it leads.

20:14.001 --> 20:17.969
Max and Sally will be with you,
infiltrating his life in their own way.

20:18.910 --> 20:21.439
Part of a new family, so to speak.

20:30.317 --> 20:33.084
Just have fun with it.

20:33.086 --> 20:34.119
I'm sure I will.

20:34.121 --> 20:36.454
Welcome to the family.

21:08.024 --> 21:11.126
[phone buzzing]

21:11.128 --> 21:12.928
- Hello?
- <i>Yeah, it's Max.</i>

21:12.930 --> 21:14.596
<i>- The location has changed.
- Why is that?</i>

21:14.598 --> 21:16.149
<i>Your dad and I thought it would be best</i>

21:16.233 --> 21:18.133
<i>if we took the conversation
out of the house.</i>

21:18.135 --> 21:20.389
We're at the Roundabout Inn in Bowville.

21:20.471 --> 21:21.748
<i>It's just outside of town.</i>

21:21.839 --> 21:23.705
<i>Apparently, they serve the best pancakes</i>

21:23.707 --> 21:25.874
in Indiana, so follow the plan.

21:25.876 --> 21:27.309
<i>You might even get a
chance to enjoy them.</i>

21:27.311 --> 21:28.977
Let me speak to my father.

21:32.383 --> 21:34.216
- Ezie?
- <i>Are you okay?</i>

21:34.218 --> 21:36.385
Dad, what... what's going on?

21:36.387 --> 21:37.263
I'm fine.

21:37.355 --> 21:40.656
Everything here is going
as civilly as possible.

21:40.658 --> 21:41.757
<i>You are not to worry.</i>

21:41.809 --> 21:43.008
How do you expect me not to worry?

21:43.010 --> 21:44.710
<i>Just don't! You're a Bloom.</i>

21:44.712 --> 21:47.479
When things get tough,
stick your head up and...

21:47.481 --> 21:48.981
Put your shoulders back.

21:48.983 --> 21:50.983
Yeah, I got it, Dad. I got it.

21:52.110 --> 21:53.218
I'll be with you soon, okay?

21:53.220 --> 21:55.354
All right, good.

21:55.873 --> 21:57.099
Ezra.

21:57.134 --> 21:58.824
<i>Keep your wits about you.</i>

21:58.826 --> 22:00.859
I will.

22:05.733 --> 22:08.734
<i>[soft, tense music]</i>

22:08.736 --> 22:15.874
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:21.515 --> 22:23.382
How long you been in this line of work?

22:23.973 --> 22:25.084
Almost 40 years.

22:25.086 --> 22:26.785
Hmm.

22:26.787 --> 22:28.887
How about you?

22:31.225 --> 22:33.659
We've both been at it a while.

22:34.691 --> 22:36.895
I knew a con man once.

22:37.710 --> 22:39.832
Guy I grew up with, Gabe Singer.

22:39.834 --> 22:41.400
He'd dress up like a rabbi

22:41.402 --> 22:45.170
and go door-to-door
selling Torah scrolls.

22:45.172 --> 22:48.744
Said they'd been pulled
from the floorboards

22:48.779 --> 22:50.656
of homes in the Warsaw ghetto.

22:50.691 --> 22:52.711
Precious relics.

22:52.713 --> 22:54.847
They were just cheap rip-offs.

22:54.849 --> 22:58.083
He'd pour coffee on them,
kick them around in the dirt.

22:58.085 --> 22:59.718
And people bought 'em.

22:59.720 --> 23:01.086
They believed.

23:01.803 --> 23:03.088
They wanted to believe.

23:03.649 --> 23:05.858
Innocent people.

23:09.193 --> 23:11.389
I don't know how you
people can do what you do.

23:11.424 --> 23:13.032
I don't know how people
can steal a patent

23:13.067 --> 23:13.799
from their own brother

23:13.801 --> 23:15.100
and then have him institutionalized.

23:15.102 --> 23:16.635
Hey, you want to know something?

23:16.637 --> 23:17.970
It's not that simple.

23:17.972 --> 23:19.471
I'm sure it was very complicated.

23:19.473 --> 23:21.473
As a matter of fact, it was.

23:21.475 --> 23:23.876
Haven't I been punished enough?

23:28.190 --> 23:30.750
Looks like you've been
punished too, yeah?

23:30.785 --> 23:33.105
What happened? Some poor sucker
finally catch up to you?

23:33.140 --> 23:35.898
Hey, cool it with the 20 Questions.

23:35.933 --> 23:39.391
- No, why don't you tell him?
- What?

23:39.393 --> 23:41.860
Why don't you tell him
what happened, Max?

23:43.896 --> 23:46.865
- I don't know what happened, Sally.
- Why don't you guess?

23:59.179 --> 24:01.012
So what do you think the chances are

24:01.014 --> 24:02.914
that Margaret Jonson
actually drops a dime

24:02.916 --> 24:04.082
on her own daughter?

24:04.084 --> 24:06.184
What would you do? You're a father.

24:06.186 --> 24:08.053
Our girl's in trouble.

24:08.055 --> 24:10.722
Yeah, but I like to think
that I raised them well enough

24:10.724 --> 24:12.491
that they wouldn't become con artists.

24:12.493 --> 24:15.193
That's just me.

24:16.070 --> 24:17.562
You never know.

24:18.932 --> 24:21.099
What's that supposed to mean?

24:21.883 --> 24:23.568
I'm the oldest of three.

24:23.570 --> 24:25.403
My brother Ray, the youngest,

24:25.405 --> 24:28.240
like me, crossed "T"s, dotted "I"s.

24:28.242 --> 24:30.675
Lives in Woodbridge, New Jersey.

24:30.677 --> 24:32.210
Is a high school principal.

24:32.212 --> 24:34.179
Married a cardiologist.

24:34.181 --> 24:36.915
Then there's our sister, June.

24:36.928 --> 24:39.784
Same parents, same love,
same everything.

24:39.786 --> 24:43.455
She set our grandparents'
house on fire when she was 10,

24:43.457 --> 24:48.126
ran away to Los Angeles
when she was barely 15,

24:48.128 --> 24:53.064
found face down in a reservoir
two days before she turned 20.

24:53.066 --> 24:55.400
Jesus.

24:55.402 --> 24:57.636
Sometimes it's about
the way you're raised.

24:57.638 --> 24:59.104
Sometimes it's about the genes.

24:59.106 --> 25:03.041
And sometimes it's
just so goddamn crazy,

25:03.043 --> 25:05.677
we don't have a say in it.

25:05.736 --> 25:08.280
Pretending otherwise
will drive you crazy.

25:10.884 --> 25:12.450
Let's get the check.

25:12.452 --> 25:14.252
And then to the Blooms'.

25:14.254 --> 25:15.754
Well, tomorrow morning?

25:15.756 --> 25:17.489
It's been a long drive.

25:17.491 --> 25:19.057
It's time to get some rest.

25:19.059 --> 25:22.093
Check, please?

25:22.095 --> 25:23.361
And you, my dear,

25:23.363 --> 25:27.065
should probably call your kids.

25:27.067 --> 25:29.100
Heading into Indianapolis?

25:29.102 --> 25:31.136
Uh, tomorrow.

25:31.138 --> 25:34.005
Tonight we're just gonna
find a hotel and sack out.

25:34.007 --> 25:36.341
- All right.
- You got any recommendations?

25:36.343 --> 25:37.676
There's a place called the Roundabout

25:37.678 --> 25:38.740
two exits down.

25:38.746 --> 25:41.146
People say they serve the
best pancakes in the state.

25:41.148 --> 25:42.314
Oh, really? Have you tried them?

25:42.316 --> 25:44.249
I don't eat gluten.

25:46.353 --> 25:48.920
<i>[percussive intro]</i>

25:48.922 --> 25:52.157
<i>♪ It is what it is ♪</i>

25:52.159 --> 25:55.026
Damn, this is a sexy-ass vehicle.

25:55.028 --> 25:57.162
There's, like, 20 speakers in here.

25:57.164 --> 26:00.131
Really feel the bass line
up in your donkey-donk, huh?

26:00.133 --> 26:03.935
Mm. ♪ Oh, yeah ♪

26:03.937 --> 26:05.470
<i>♪ Well, well, well,
well, well, well ♪</i>

26:05.472 --> 26:07.539
You want to know what I
love about these cars?

26:07.541 --> 26:09.140
What do you love about these cars?

26:09.142 --> 26:10.508
They're body-on-frame.

26:10.510 --> 26:12.310
Ooh, that sounds fun.

26:12.312 --> 26:13.478
It <i> is</i> fun.

26:13.480 --> 26:14.613
I don't mean to mansplain.

26:14.615 --> 26:15.847
You probably know that, right?

26:15.849 --> 26:16.948
Is that why you got it?

26:16.950 --> 26:19.117
The 6.2 V8

26:19.119 --> 26:23.154
or, what, the shale interiors
with the cocoa accents?

26:23.156 --> 26:24.956
Actually, I just got it

26:24.958 --> 26:26.858
'cause it was the most
expensive one they had.

26:26.860 --> 26:28.860
Mm, I love that.

26:28.862 --> 26:32.297
So tell me something about
little sis I don't know.

26:32.299 --> 26:33.565
Ooh, my goodness.

26:33.567 --> 26:34.799
Where to start?

26:34.801 --> 26:36.835
N-o spells "no."

26:36.837 --> 26:40.205
Did you know that this
cool downtown artist

26:40.207 --> 26:42.874
was once a very serious equestrian?

26:42.876 --> 26:44.309
- Oh, what?
- One year riding.

26:44.311 --> 26:46.544
- Two state championships.
- Wow.

26:46.546 --> 26:48.213
- Then she quit.
- Poppy.

26:48.215 --> 26:49.714
Jules fell off the horse and quit.

26:49.716 --> 26:51.316
I did not fall off the horse.

26:51.318 --> 26:53.151
Her name was Banner,
and she broke her leg,

26:53.153 --> 26:54.319
and they put her down,

26:54.321 --> 26:56.821
and I didn't want to ride anymore.

26:56.823 --> 26:59.157
[sighs]

26:59.159 --> 27:01.092
Damn!

27:01.094 --> 27:04.029
Riding in a Caddy with
a couple of horse girls.

27:04.031 --> 27:05.330
Could be worse.

27:05.332 --> 27:07.032
Yee-ha.

27:13.382 --> 27:14.880
_

27:18.211 --> 27:20.679
Foreclosed?

27:21.882 --> 27:24.049
What the hell?

27:24.051 --> 27:25.050
Oh, no, no, no...

27:25.052 --> 27:26.051
Is that normal?

27:26.053 --> 27:27.786
No, no, no, no.

27:27.788 --> 27:30.889
Oh, my God.

27:36.033 --> 27:37.334
<i>What happened, Richie?</i>

27:37.425 --> 27:39.429
Weren't you paying the mortgage?

27:41.928 --> 27:43.895
I was behind on a few payments,

27:43.897 --> 27:46.564
and I was waiting
until we sold the ring.

27:46.566 --> 27:50.101
We had to go to Mexico, and...

27:50.103 --> 27:52.103
God damn it, Richie.

27:52.105 --> 27:53.805
You stupid idiot!

27:53.807 --> 27:55.573
God! Stupid, stupid, stupid!

27:55.575 --> 27:58.377
Okay, okay,
let's just go inside and check

27:58.399 --> 27:59.598
before we totally freak out.

27:59.600 --> 28:01.900
No, no, no, we cannot go inside,

28:01.902 --> 28:03.735
because they probably showed
whoever's in there our photos,

28:03.737 --> 28:06.271
and we'll be those idiot criminals
returning to the scene of the crime.

28:06.273 --> 28:07.506
I can go in.

28:07.508 --> 28:09.074
Yeah! She can go in.

28:09.076 --> 28:11.176
[sighs] Wait.

28:11.918 --> 28:14.279
I can't let you go in there alone.

28:16.092 --> 28:17.382
Jesus Christ.

28:22.923 --> 28:25.924
<i>[playful jazzy music]</i>

28:25.926 --> 28:29.027
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:29.439 --> 28:30.505
Afternoon, folks.

28:30.507 --> 28:31.539
Afternoon.

28:31.541 --> 28:32.907
JTS, Sun Briar Realty.

28:32.909 --> 28:34.709
Archer Sutton. This is my wife.

28:34.711 --> 28:36.511
- Ellie Sutton.
- Hello.

28:36.513 --> 28:38.346
Well, Ellie, Archer,

28:38.348 --> 28:40.949
you have hit the jackpot with this one.

28:40.951 --> 28:43.385
This two-bedroom, one-family beauty

28:43.387 --> 28:46.955
just went on public auction for $25,000.

28:46.957 --> 28:48.623
Yeah, that's how much
is left on the mortgage

28:48.625 --> 28:49.891
from the previous owner.

28:49.893 --> 28:51.226
Shit, man.

28:51.228 --> 28:52.260
I'm sorry?

28:52.262 --> 28:54.095
We just can't believe

28:54.097 --> 28:57.799
houses for public auction go
for such absurdly low prices.

28:57.801 --> 28:59.801
Truth is, he's on the board
at the Kenner Club,

28:59.803 --> 29:02.604
so this will be something of
a winter sanctuary for us.

29:02.606 --> 29:04.472
Such a lovely sanctuary.

29:04.474 --> 29:06.541
I'm not sure about these ceilings,
though.

29:06.543 --> 29:08.777
Well, yeah, not the grandest, but...

29:08.779 --> 29:10.712
Add some cove lighting,
vertical paneling...

29:10.714 --> 29:11.780
You know, cove...

29:11.782 --> 29:12.914
Lower set sofas,

29:12.916 --> 29:14.382
maybe widen the windows, right?

29:14.384 --> 29:16.384
Yeah, yeah, definitely.

29:16.386 --> 29:18.086
Honey, I'm gonna take a walk around.

29:18.088 --> 29:20.054
You guys work all that out.

29:20.056 --> 29:21.190
Yes, darling.

29:21.292 --> 29:25.560
So why don't you show me
where these bathrooms are?

29:25.562 --> 29:27.695
Well, the bathroom
is right down the hall.

29:27.697 --> 29:30.598
I'm sorry; did you say "the bathroom"?

29:45.015 --> 29:48.850
<i>[gentle piano music]</i>

29:48.852 --> 29:50.852
[sighs]

29:50.854 --> 29:57.926
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:11.537 --> 30:12.607
Any luck?

30:12.609 --> 30:14.309
Uh, yeah, I actually found it.

30:14.311 --> 30:16.177
I'm just really into
digging into this garbage

30:16.179 --> 30:18.346
with my bare hands.

30:20.984 --> 30:23.017
[sighs]

30:25.856 --> 30:27.155
Hey.

30:27.157 --> 30:29.457
It's okay. We'll work it out.

30:29.459 --> 30:32.126
Yeah. Let's just go.

30:32.128 --> 30:33.761
There's nothing left for me here.

30:49.149 --> 30:51.083
No. Hey, absolutely...
Get this out of here.

30:51.181 --> 30:53.481
Come on; it's just like you
but with personality.

30:53.483 --> 30:55.016
So he said everything
of value in the house

30:55.018 --> 30:57.051
was put up for auction and sold.

30:57.053 --> 30:59.153
Oh, man. Well, that's it, then.

30:59.155 --> 31:00.755
Shit.

31:00.757 --> 31:02.624
Hopefully,
Ezra's doing better than we are.

31:02.626 --> 31:04.759
Drama queens.

31:04.761 --> 31:06.728
What do you do when
you fall off a horse?

31:06.730 --> 31:07.862
Shoot it.

31:13.992 --> 31:16.404
I'll get the rooms. You get the bags.

31:19.843 --> 31:22.043
I'm grabbing ice and some drinks.

31:28.285 --> 31:30.485
[scattered conversations]

31:36.822 --> 31:40.395
Two separate rooms,
each with a queen-size bed.

31:41.328 --> 31:43.264
We only have two twins left.

31:43.266 --> 31:44.899
Excuse me?

31:44.901 --> 31:45.934
We only have...

31:45.936 --> 31:47.635
Ice machine?

31:47.637 --> 31:49.404
All the way down that way.

31:49.406 --> 31:51.172
Thanks.

31:53.398 --> 31:55.242
Just give me whatever
you have left. Thank you.

31:55.279 --> 31:57.745
Well, have Mommy take a picture of it

31:57.747 --> 31:59.881
and send it to Daddy,
and I'll make it my screensaver.

32:08.930 --> 32:09.958
Are you kidding?

32:09.960 --> 32:12.827
Those pancakes better be
worth writing home about.

32:12.829 --> 32:14.128
Kitchen's closed.

32:14.130 --> 32:15.797
We're putting in new sprinklers.

32:15.799 --> 32:17.165
May I have some change, please?

32:19.120 --> 32:21.803
If that's for another guest,
I need their signature.

32:22.401 --> 32:24.138
You can't sign for them.

32:30.947 --> 32:33.514
Sir, did you want change?

32:41.560 --> 32:42.624
Mrs. Jonson?

32:45.804 --> 32:46.506
What is it?

32:46.530 --> 32:48.514
I just saw that goddamn FBI agent,

32:48.549 --> 32:49.530
- that Angie lady.
- What?

32:49.532 --> 32:51.199
Shit, Patrick's there too.

32:51.201 --> 32:52.634
Look, he's right there.

32:52.636 --> 32:53.935
- Is she there now?
- <i>Yes.</i>

32:53.937 --> 32:55.545
She's planning on spending the night.

32:55.580 --> 32:56.638
After that, I don't know.

32:56.640 --> 32:57.939
<i>We'll be there as fast as we can,</i>

32:57.941 --> 33:00.475
and I promise you we will keep her safe.

33:01.349 --> 33:02.944
I should go.

33:05.115 --> 33:06.347
[sighs]

33:06.349 --> 33:07.949
What's up?

33:07.951 --> 33:09.117
That was Margaret Jonson.

33:09.119 --> 33:11.519
Maddie's home.

33:11.521 --> 33:13.554
Your wife or your stupid
son called the cops.

33:13.556 --> 33:14.756
That was your plan, you idiot?

33:14.758 --> 33:15.823
What? No!

33:15.825 --> 33:17.458
I swear to God I will hurt you

33:17.460 --> 33:18.693
in ways you cannot imagine!

33:18.695 --> 33:19.827
Wait, wait, wait, wait, Sally.

33:19.829 --> 33:22.664
Are they leaving? Look.

33:22.666 --> 33:24.298
- [sighs]
- They're leaving.

33:24.300 --> 33:26.200
Well, if she thinks you made her,

33:26.202 --> 33:27.835
of course they're leaving,
and they'll send the cops!

33:27.837 --> 33:29.671
Just take it easy.

33:29.673 --> 33:31.005
We're leaving as soon
as they're out of here.

33:33.309 --> 33:36.010
[screaming]

33:44.760 --> 33:47.155
I'm not sitting back for (BLEEP) crooks!

33:47.157 --> 33:48.956
Get your hands off me.

33:50.493 --> 33:53.261
[yelling]

34:01.748 --> 34:03.004
- Calm down.
- Let me out!

34:03.006 --> 34:04.872
- Calm down!
- Let me out!

34:04.874 --> 34:07.108
Arthur, stop!

34:07.110 --> 34:09.177
[both panting]

34:10.780 --> 34:14.614
- Oh, my God.
- Oh, Jesus Christ.

34:14.617 --> 34:16.717
It's like the whole
goddamn thing is in there.

34:16.719 --> 34:18.886
- All right, don't move.
- Okay.

34:18.888 --> 34:21.355
- [screams]
- Idiot.

34:21.357 --> 34:23.558
Let me see it.

34:23.560 --> 34:25.793
Oh, God, we need to clean this.

34:25.795 --> 34:29.163
We'll use hand soap for now.
Come on. Come on.

34:29.974 --> 34:32.132
Arthur, are you calm in there?

34:32.650 --> 34:35.303
I need soap and a towel
and no more bullshit.

34:36.313 --> 34:37.938
Come on, schmuck. Answer me.

34:37.940 --> 34:40.007
Or I'll let Sally have her way with you.

34:41.745 --> 34:44.277
What the (BLEEP)?

34:58.928 --> 35:00.962
Well, shit.

35:06.312 --> 35:09.385
Son of a bitch. God damn it.

35:09.387 --> 35:11.020
This was not supposed to happen.

35:11.022 --> 35:12.455
People were not supposed to die.

35:12.457 --> 35:13.756
He did it to himself.

35:13.758 --> 35:15.024
No, no, this whole thing,

35:15.026 --> 35:17.460
this whole goddamn
thing is out of control.

35:17.462 --> 35:19.095
We're grifters; we're not killers.

35:19.097 --> 35:20.897
Hey, get your shit together,
God damn it.

35:20.899 --> 35:22.699
Calm down.

35:22.701 --> 35:24.901
Maybe you should ask
Heller if we're killers.

35:24.903 --> 35:27.237
And I don't recall you
getting down on your knees

35:27.239 --> 35:29.706
when you put me in that
car with Lenny Cohen.

35:29.708 --> 35:31.241
Rules of the game, Max.

35:31.243 --> 35:32.876
That's how it goes.

35:32.878 --> 35:36.779
So pull yourself together,
and act like a friggin' professional.

35:39.050 --> 35:41.451
<i>And the fullback right up the middle.</i>

35:41.453 --> 35:43.720
<i>Gain of two on the play.</i>

35:43.722 --> 35:45.321
<i>That'll bring up third...</i>

35:45.323 --> 35:47.891
Ah, there's that face.

35:47.893 --> 35:49.459
[laughs] Hi.

35:49.461 --> 35:50.493
[laughs]

35:50.495 --> 35:51.995
Maddie, Dad.

35:51.997 --> 35:53.163
Maddie.

35:53.165 --> 35:54.664
It's so good to see you.

35:55.198 --> 35:56.733
How's my girl?

35:56.735 --> 35:58.735
I'm good, Dad. How are you?

35:58.737 --> 36:00.136
Oh, you know.

36:00.138 --> 36:03.106
Little cabin fever.

36:03.108 --> 36:05.909
Happy to still be watching
the wheels go round and round.

36:05.911 --> 36:08.444
I get it, Dad.

36:08.446 --> 36:10.980
So what's new, hmm? How's Finland?

36:10.982 --> 36:13.249
Uh, Greenland?

36:13.251 --> 36:17.020
You look a little tired, sweetie.

36:17.022 --> 36:20.623
Well, things haven't been so great.

36:20.625 --> 36:22.659
Oh, no? Come on; tell me.

36:22.661 --> 36:27.730
Come into my... my office here.

36:31.002 --> 36:33.136
It's, um...

36:35.273 --> 36:38.274
Dad, I've been working

36:38.276 --> 36:42.545
for a very bad person.

36:42.547 --> 36:47.217
I've done some pretty bad things.

36:47.219 --> 36:49.485
Tricked people,

36:49.487 --> 36:54.357
taken their money, hurt them.

36:54.359 --> 36:57.961
I want to stop.

36:57.963 --> 36:59.996
I want to be free of it.

36:59.998 --> 37:02.665
You've always been so determined.

37:02.667 --> 37:06.035
You know, you... you...
you put your mind into something,

37:06.037 --> 37:08.371
watch out.

37:08.373 --> 37:12.375
Thanks for saying that, Dad.

37:12.377 --> 37:13.543
Hey, can I tell you something?

37:13.545 --> 37:14.657
Mm-hmm.

37:14.746 --> 37:16.372
It's a secret. You can't tell anyone.

37:16.482 --> 37:18.248
Okay.

37:18.340 --> 37:23.653
You know this man I work for,
the Doctor?

37:23.655 --> 37:26.022
I'm gonna kill him.

37:28.159 --> 37:33.663
It's the only way for me to get out,

37:33.665 --> 37:35.231
be free.

37:37.902 --> 37:40.003
Hi.

37:40.005 --> 37:42.905
There's that face.

37:43.908 --> 37:47.844
Hi, Dad.

37:47.846 --> 37:50.046
I'm gonna go downstairs
and check on dinner, okay?

37:50.048 --> 37:51.748
Okay, great.

37:58.696 --> 38:01.090
- Max.
- Hey.

38:06.547 --> 38:08.931
Hold on. Hold on. I'm sorry.

38:12.137 --> 38:14.037
I didn't know what I was walking into.

38:14.039 --> 38:16.272
Ah, don't worry about it.
Don't worry about it.

38:16.274 --> 38:18.941
Look, we had a problem here.

38:18.943 --> 38:20.243
I'm very sorry.

38:20.245 --> 38:22.211
It wasn't supposed to go down this way.

38:48.473 --> 38:50.239
What did you do to him?

38:50.241 --> 38:52.308
- Kid...
- What did you do to him?

38:59.137 --> 39:01.939
<i>[soft music]</i>

39:01.941 --> 39:09.013
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:21.635 --> 39:23.093
All right, kid.

39:23.095 --> 39:25.429
It's time to go.

39:30.102 --> 39:32.169
I'm sorry.

39:32.171 --> 39:34.338
Hey, Ezra.

39:43.933 --> 39:46.984
Come on. Come on.

39:48.120 --> 39:50.254
Come on.

39:53.125 --> 39:56.360
Okay, come.

40:12.645 --> 40:15.279
<i>♪ I may not know ♪</i>

40:15.281 --> 40:18.148
<i>♪ What happens now ♪</i>

40:18.150 --> 40:23.787
<i>♪ I see some old
cracks in your ground ♪</i>

40:23.789 --> 40:26.623
<i>♪ If I could fall ♪</i>

40:26.625 --> 40:29.359
<i>♪ Into your arms ♪</i>

40:29.361 --> 40:34.665
<i>♪ Sweet-loving maid,
I swear I did no harm ♪</i>

40:34.667 --> 40:36.266
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:36.268 --> 40:40.904
<i>♪ Hold your hands up high ♪</i>

40:40.906 --> 40:46.343
<i>♪ My love, I'll see you by and by ♪</i>

40:46.345 --> 40:47.644
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:47.646 --> 40:49.146
<i>♪ Hold ♪</i>

40:49.148 --> 40:52.583
Rise and shine, Jujube. We made it.

40:52.585 --> 40:58.489
<i>♪ My love, I'll see you by and by ♪</i>

40:58.491 --> 41:00.090
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:00.092 --> 41:02.025
Oh, wow.

41:02.027 --> 41:03.227
This is no cabin.

41:03.229 --> 41:04.895
This is a friggin' starter castle.

41:04.897 --> 41:07.898
Come on. I want to show you around.

41:07.900 --> 41:10.367
Don't worry, guys. I got the bags.

42:09.628 --> 42:11.695
Coffee in the cold.

42:11.797 --> 42:13.797
Coffee in the cold.

